description:
NEW: Now feature Rotary Encoder with Button!
I have made some Compact Versions of some things that i frequently used in my projects.
Info: Will install marcoaita/malibrary for the Buzzer Node
name: compact-utils

HJF8vBcs54.description: Board GPIO port with LCD D7 pin
HJF8vBcs54.label: D7

Hk4Ivrqo94.description: Board GPIO port with LCD D5 pin
Hk4Ivrqo94.label: D5

SyOUvrqjqE.description: Board GPIO port with LCD RS pin
SyOUvrqjqE.label: RS

r1G8vrqi5N.description: Board GPIO port with LCD D6 pin
r1G8vrqi5N.label: D6

r1UUDH5s54.description: Board GPIO port with LCD EN pin
r1UUDH5s54.label: EN

rkeIDrqjqV.description: Board GPIO port with LCD D4 pin
rkeIDrqjqV.label: D4

@/compact-number-check.description: Checks if Number is equal to the other and outputs in pulses of true and false

@/compact-rtc-all-inclusive.description:
Reads from RTC device.
OUTPUTS: Hour:Minute:Seconds
You can change the spcers between the Numbers with the SYM PIN.

rJF7cEc5V.description: When to read from the rtc device
rJF7cEc5V.label: READ

@/constant-pulser.description:
Gives constant Ticks when set
(RST ON BOOT)

ByrYhlVcc4.description: Setting the FlipFlop thus emitting consatnt signal
ByrYhlVcc4.label: SET

rybt3eEqqV.description: Resets the FlipFlop thus not putting a signal out
rybt3eEqqV.label: RES

@/cycled-buzzer.description:
When activated it will set a puls to the buzzer for the amount of time you set.
NEEDS: marcoaita/malibrary

HyLnlRyzoN.description:
If need to be activated on True
(SET PIN FALSE TO TRUE WHEN USING TRUE PIN!!)
HyLnlRyzoN.label: True

r1HhgRkGs4.description: Will set the amount of Times it will cicle
r1HhgRkGs4.label: Rep

rJchl0yGsN.description:
If need activated on a False puls.
(IF USING TRUE PIN  SET THIS PIN TO TRUE!!)
rJchl0yGsN.label: False

@/rtc-debug.description:
(Intended to be used in DEBUG MODE) 
Used for setting up the rtc device and getting a check that everything worked.
Connect a watch Node and a TWEAK PULS node to puls and out PIN

ByqOuEq5N.description:
This PIN is used to activate the write.
Check that everything is correct :-)
ByqOuEq5N.label: PULS

@/time-rtc-device.description: Gets Time from Rtc Device and JOINS them with a : or what you like

HJEN7jgfi4.description: Equals to `true` while the SW button is pressed (hold down) and `false` while it is released.
HJEN7jgfi4.label: SW OP

ryIN7jgMjE.label: SW
ryIN7jgMjE.description:
The SW Pin
(If it has a switch)

@/rotary-encoder-button.description: This is used for when you have an rotary encoder with DT, CLK (and SW) Pins
